<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="problem-box">
            <div class="problem-label">Problem</div>
            <div class="problem-text">A point source of light is located <strong>25 cm</strong> in front of a single refracting surface with a power of <strong>+8.00 D</strong>. The surface separates air (n = 1.00) from glass (n = 1.50). What is the vergence of light leaving the surface?</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="diagram-section">
            <svg width="480" height="200" viewBox="0 0 480 200">
                <!-- Optical axis -->
                <line x1="20" y1="100" x2="460" y2="100" stroke="#ccc" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
                
                <!-- Refracting surface -->
                <line x1="180" y1="30" x2="180" y2="170" stroke="#1a1a1a" stroke-width="2"/>
                <text x="185" y="25" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="10" fill="#1a1a1a">F = +8.00 D</text>
                
                <!-- Object point -->
                <circle cx="60" cy="100" r="4" fill="#3b9fe7"/>
                <line x1="60" y1="100" x2="60" y2="70" stroke="#3b9fe7" stroke-width="2"/>
                <polygon points="60,70 56,78 64,78" fill="#3b9fe7"/>
                <text x="60" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="10" fill="#3b9fe7">Object</text>
                
                <!-- Diverging rays (in air) -->
                <line x1="60" y1="100" x2="180" y2="60" stroke="#3b9fe7" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="60" y1="100" x2="180" y2="100" stroke="#3b9fe7" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="60" y1="100" x2="180" y2="140" stroke="#3b9fe7" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                
                <!-- Converging rays (in glass) -->
                <line x1="180" y1="60" x2="370" y2="100" stroke="#1a1a1a" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="180" y1="100" x2="370" y2="100" stroke="#1a1a1a" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="180" y1="140" x2="370" y2="100" stroke="#1a1a1a" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                
                <!-- Image point -->
                <circle cx="370" cy="100" r="4" fill="#1a1a1a" fill-opacity="0.5" stroke="#1a1a1a" stroke-width="1"/>
                <text x="370" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="10" fill="#666">Image</text>
                
                <!-- Object distance bracket -->
                <line x1="60" y1="160" x2="180" y2="160" stroke="#666" stroke-width="1"/>
                <line x1="60" y1="155" x2="60" y2="165" stroke="#666" stroke-width="1"/>
                <line x1="180" y1="155" x2="180" y2="165" stroke="#666" stroke-width="1"/>
                <text x="120" y="178" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="11" fill="#666">l = −25 cm</text>
                
                <!-- Medium labels -->
                <text x="40" y="45" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="11" fill="#666">n = 1.00</text>
                <text x="40" y="58" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="10" fill="#888">(air)</text>
                
                <text x="400" y="45" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="11" fill="#666">n' = 1.50</text>
                <text x="400" y="58" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="10" fill="#888">(glass)</text>
                
                <!-- Vergence labels -->
                <text x="100" y="50" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="11" fill="#3b9fe7" font-weight="500">L = −4.00 D</text>
                <text x="260" y="50" font-family="Work Sans" font-size="11" fill="#1a1a1a" font-weight="500">L' = ?</text>
            </svg>
        </div>
        
        <div class="key-formulae">
            <div class="key-formulae-title">KEY FORMULAE</div>
            <div class="key-formulae-item">Vergence relationship: <span class="var">L'</span> = <span class="var">L</span> + <span class="var">F</span></div>
            <div class="key-formulae-item">Object vergence: <span class="var">L</span> = <span class="var">n</span> / <span class="var">l</span></div>
            <div class="key-formulae-item">Image vergence: <span class="var">L'</span> = <span class="var">n'</span> / <span class="var">l'</span></div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-title">Step 1: Find the object vergence (L)</div>
        <p>Vergence is the reciprocal of distance, adjusted for the refractive index of the medium. Light diverging from a real object has negative vergence. Using the object vergence formula:</p>
        <div class="formula">
            <span class="var">L</span> = <span class="var">n</span> / <span class="var">l</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="variable-list">
            <li><strong>n</strong> = refractive index of object space (air = 1.00)</li>
            <li><strong>l</strong> = object distance = −0.25 m (negative, as object is to the left)</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="calc-row">L = 1.00 / (−0.25 m) = <strong>−4.00 D</strong></div>
        <p>The negative vergence indicates light is diverging from the object.</p>
        
        <div class="section-title">Step 2: Apply the vergence relationship</div>
        <p>As light passes through the refracting surface, the surface power is added to the incident vergence to yield the emergent vergence:</p>
        <div class="formula">
            <span class="var">L'</span> = <span class="var">L</span> + <span class="var">F</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-row">L' = −4.00 D + (+8.00 D)</div>
        
        <div class="final-answer">
            L' = <span class="result">+4.00 D</span>
        </div>
        
        <p style="margin-top: 16px;">The positive emergent vergence indicates the light is now converging after refraction. If we wanted to find where the image forms, we could use L' = n'/l' to solve for l' = 1.50 / 4.00 = 0.375 m = 37.5 cm to the right of the surface.</p>
    </div>
